    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Irate Americans Get Gas Masks</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">AP</byline>
      <dateline>RIYADH, Saudi Arabia, Jan. 29</dateline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Bowing to pressure from angry Americans and their elected representatives back home, the United States Embassy said today that it would offer gas masks to American citizens in Saudi Arabia.</p>
        <p>It said the masks, obtained from military stocks, would be handed out as long as the supply lasted. But American diplomats made it clear that they believe fears of a chemical attack on the Saudi capital were unfounded.</p>
        <p>Diplomatic sources, insisting on anonymity, said some American residents had complained to senators and congressional representatives, who in turn demanded an explanation of the embassy policy of not providing gas masks.</p>
      </block>
